parameters.name: UT
parameters.description: Universal Time given in PDS format: yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss.sss.

parameters.name: PCOS
parameters.description:
Amplitude of spin ripple on P sensor in      
  phase with sun pulse signal.

parameters.name: PSIN
parameters.description:
Amplitude of spin ripple on P sensor in      
  quadrature with sun pulse signal.

parameters.name: DX
parameters.description:
Difference between amplitudes at spin        
  period on the T sensor and G sensor that should be parallel to each         
  other (quadrature component on T and in phase on G).

parameters.name: DY
parameters.description:
Difference between the second pair of        
  amplitudes at spin frequency that are parallel on the G and T sensors.      
  These two amplitudes have a phase of 90 degrees to that of the DX pair.

parameters.name: DZ
parameters.description:
Difference between the average field along   
  the G sensor and the average along the P sensor.  This difference           
  should not change if the ambient field changes.

parameters.name: RAMP
parameters.description:
The output of the 3 non-orthogonal sensors   
  can be combined to give 3 orthogonal pseudosensor output S1, S2, S3 in      
  the equatorial X-Y plane and along the Z or spin axis.  RAMP measures       
  the ratio of the amplitudes of the sine waves in the X-Y plane measured     
  by pseudosensors 1 and 2.  Should be unity.

parameters.name: DPHS
parameters.description:
Measures the phase difference between the    
  output of pseudosensors S1 and S2.

parameters.name: DC1
parameters.description: The average field seen by S1.

parameters.name: DC2
parameters.description: The average field seen by S2.

parameters.name: ZCOS
parameters.description:
The cosine amplitude, after spin frequency,  
  seen along pseudosensor 3.  It should be zero.

parameters.name: ZSIN
parameters.description:
The sine amplitude at the spin frequency     
  seen along pseudosensor 3.  It should be zero.

parameters.name: ZDC
parameters.description: The average field seen along pseudosensor 3.
